.th GRPNT VII 18-March-1980
.sh NAME
grpnt \*- read a point from a GRINNELL window
.sh SYNOPSIS
int
.bd grpnt
(area, cnum, rnum)
.s3
int area[16];
.br
int cnum;
.br
int rnum;
.sh DESCRIPTION
.it Grpnt
is used to read in the value of one point from
user's  window.  The  value  of the
function, if no error has occurred, will be from 0 to 4095 when
reading an image channel.
.it Cnum
and
.it rnum
are the window-relative column and row for the point to read.
.it Area
is the buffer from the
.it gopen
call.
.s3
A negative value indicates an error (nothing done).
.sh DIAGNOSTICS
.sh FILES
/dev/gr
.sh "SEE ALSO"
gopen(VII), gwpnt(VII)
.sh AUTHOR
Russ Smith
.sh BUGS
Cannot read the overlay channel (always returns zero).
